5|$|The Assistant Commandant of <b>the</b> <b>Marine</b> <b>Corps</b> (ACMC) is {{the second}} highest-ranking officer in the United States Marine Corps, {{and serves as a}} deputy for the Commandant of <b>the</b> <b>Marine</b> <b>Corps</b> (CMC). Before 1946, the title was known as Assistant to the Commandant.|$|E
