5|$|At {{the time}} of the 1920 U.S. Census, Clarke and his wife were living in Detroit. In June 1929, Clarke rejoined <b>the</b> <b>Marine</b> <b>Corps,</b> serving until August 1932. At {{the time of}} the 1930 U.S. Census, Clarke was {{stationed}} at the Quantico Marine Barracks in Prince William County, Virginia. After being discharged from <b>the</b> <b>Marine</b> <b>Corps,</b> Clarke built a house in River Rouge, a suburb of Detroit, where he lived with his mother. In June 1949, Clarke was found dead at his home in River Rouge.|$|E
