5|$|Bolt {{attended}} the University of Florida, majoring in accounting and meeting {{most of the}} costs himself using money that he had saved while working through high school. He joined Phi Eta Sigma, an honor society and professional fraternity, and Alpha Tau Omega, a social fraternity. In 1941, his brother Bruce also enrolled at Florida, straining the family's expenses; John dropped out after his second year so that his brother could complete his degree. Bolt enlisted in <b>the</b> <b>Marine</b> <b>Corps</b> Reserve in April 1941 to train as a pilot, but deferred his training when <b>the</b> <b>Marine</b> <b>Corps</b> offered him the chance to finish college and attend law school, paying him 500 a year to do so.|$|E
